<br>
They start VERY late in a mage's career.<br>
<br>
What if PoP brought about lower level modulation type items?  It would certainly fit in the class. . .<br>
<br>
The first goal is to make these spells an actual means of regenerating mana (so, they should generate net positive mana), unlike mod rod 1.  The second goal is to make them less powerful than mod rod 2.<br>
<br>
So, I came up with items with a tick-level casting time that cast lower level modulation effects.<br>
<br>
(note: I haven't taken into effect horses.  D'oh.  Can you think of a way around this?)<br>
<br>
Here is my waky idea:<br>
<br>
L 20 spell:<br>
100 mana<br>
Summon Brazier of Modulation.<br>
4 second casting time<br>
Targetting Summon (target player gets the item).<br>
<br>
Brazier of Modulation.<br>
NO DROP LORE NO RENT EXPENDABLE<br>
PRI SEC RANGE AMMO<br>
WIZ NEC MAG ENC SHM DRU CLE<br>
10 charges of Minor Modulation (6.0 casting time, must equip)<br>
-30 HP +15 + (level/2) mana, capped at L 40 (at +35 mana for a click (don't forget -20 mana from lack of medding))<br>
<br>
Net effect: -300 HP from target, +150 mana on target, -96 to 90 mana on self (spec conj).  (counting in the lack of medding due to using the clicky)<br>
<br>
At L 20, this is -300 hp for +54 mana total, or about 5.5:1 HP-&gt;mana ratio<br>
At L 40, this is -300 hp for +60 mana total, or a 5:1 HP-&gt; mana ratio<br>
<br>
In the target, it generates 2:1 HP-&gt;mana.<br>
<br>
L 40 spell:<br>
350 mana<br>
Summon Censer of Modulation.<br>
Same specs as Brazier (targeted NO DROP summon)<br>
4.0 CT<br>
<br>
Censer of Modulation<br>
10 charges of Lesser Modulation (12.0 casting time)<br>
-100 HP +100 mana.  A 1:1 ratio spell, but in the casting you could have medding 40 mana.<br>
<br>
Net effect is -1000 HP +1000 mana (over 2 minutes), costing 400 mana in medding and 315 mana for summoning (spec conj).<br>
<br>
So, a net gain of 285 mana for 1000 hps, or a 3.5:1 HP-&gt;mana ratio<br>
<br>
This isn't as good as a mod rod 2, and much much slower.<br>
<br>
By L 60, with 24 per tick meditation, this item falls in efficiency to 5:1 HP-&gt;mana, making it a bad replacement for mod rod 3.<br>
<br>
The other large difference is that efficient heals are not yet availiable to mages -- no TOPOR, no uber efficient heals over time, and complete heal on a L 40 mage is not an efficient heal spell.<br>
<br>
Lastly, these items cannot be stocked up on the ground, but can only be stored on the players who are using them.  These spells introduce the modulation part of the mage's abilities at higher levels starting at L 20, getting the mage used to the spells.  They act more like a long term buff than an item.<br>
<br>
