<br>
Magicians are summoners with a heavy slanting of our abilities towards offensive, lacking major defense or major utility.<br>
<br>
This, however, does not mean that we have 0 utility, or that we should only be given things that increase our damage output. Our summons are what make us unique in our class, as anyone can meerly do damage.<br>
<br>
As for the idea. Kinda cool, though necessary? I doubt it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukinelaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 362<br> <font color=#333333>(10/7/02 7:27:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New MRods</span><hr size=1> Rogues have no utility ?<br>
<br>
Corpse recovery from areas you couldn't get through with invis or invis to undead alone ? Saves bundles on coffins<br>
<br>
Areas of the game you cannot even reach without a rogue to pick the locks ?<br>
<br>
Finding and disarming traps, saves alot of aggravation.<br>
<br>
I guess I won't mention poisons since that's more of a combat ability. But rogue poisons are still very nice.<br>
<br>
Magician utility:<br>
<br>
- Summoning foci, quickly becoming obsolete<br>
- CotH'ing people, still somewhat useful, but newer content is making this ability more and more restricted<br>
- Summoning rods, useful, but puts us in the boat necro's are/were in, being a mana slave is not fun<br>
- Other summons we have, I do not get called on for much. Sometimes waterstones, food, and drink, but everything else I almost never mem except to give stuff to my pet.<br>
<br>
We get one great utility ability, one other good ability that becomes less and less useful each expansion. The rest I could safely delete from my spellbook and never miss'em.<br>
<br>
The bulk of a magicians are wrapped up in offense and we are slipping in that area. It began in Kunark when druids were given a nuke on par with ours and now it seems the hammer is hanging over the final nail as enchanters are even being given nukes to rival ours. Heck, even a cleric can deal out more magic damage than we can (we beat them only efficiency, and not by that huge a margin). We need our offensive edge back. Our nukes should be right between wizards and druids (if that means wizards need better nukes to maintain their lead, than so be it), our pets should be unquestionably superior to any other classes (Not including charms here, they may make powerful pets, but carry significant risks too). This is what made the mage class great at the start, what I think attracted most, if not all of us to the class, and should be what is great about us. Strong nukes, and beefy pets, that is what we want (least I think so). Not mezzes and charms, that's what enchanters do, put stuff to sleep or make them obediant, that aint our game.<br>
<br>
Anyways, I digressed enough.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
